# Mission Control Charts Skill

This skill enables you to render interactive charts in any Mission Control chat
surface: board chat, group chat, channel threads, and planning chat.

The Mission Control UI interprets a fenced `json:chart` code block inside any
message and renders it as an interactive chart. The rest of the message is
rendered as normal Markdown.

---

## Supported chart types

| `type`   | Description                                                |
|----------|------------------------------------------------------------|
| `line`   | Line chart — burndowns, trends, cumulative flow            |
| `area`   | Area (filled) chart — velocity, throughput over time       |
| `bar`    | Bar chart — workload by agent, task counts, comparisons    |
| `pie`    | Pie chart — status breakdown, priority split               |
| `donut`  | Donut chart — same as pie, with a centred value label      |

---

## Chart spec reference

````
```json:chart
{
  "type":   "<line|area|bar|pie|donut>",
  "title":  "<optional heading shown above chart>",
  "xKey":   "<field name used as X axis or pie label>",
  "yKeys":  "<field name, or array of field names, for Y values>",
  "xLabel": "<optional X axis label>",
  "yLabel": "<optional Y axis label>",
  "data":   [ { "<xKey>": "...", "<yKey>": 0 } ],
  "colors": ["<optional hex or CSS colour overrides, one per series>"],
  "height": 260
}
```
````

**Required fields**: `type`, `xKey`, `yKeys`, `data`.

All values mapped by `yKeys` **must be numbers**. The `xKey` dimension is the
category/label (string or number both fine).

---

## Examples

### Sprint burndown

````
```json:chart
{
  "type": "line",
  "title": "Sprint Burndown",
  "xKey": "day",
  "yKeys": ["remaining", "ideal"],
  "xLabel": "Day",
  "yLabel": "Story Points",
  "data": [
    {"day": "Mon", "remaining": 24, "ideal": 20},
    {"day": "Tue", "remaining": 19, "ideal": 16},
    {"day": "Wed", "remaining": 15, "ideal": 12},
    {"day": "Thu", "remaining": 10, "ideal":  8},
    {"day": "Fri", "remaining":  4, "ideal":  4}
  ]
}
```
````

### Task status breakdown

````
```json:chart
{
  "type": "pie",
  "title": "Task Status",
  "xKey": "status",
  "yKeys": ["count"],
  "data": [
    {"status": "done",        "count": 12},
    {"status": "in_progress", "count":  5},
    {"status": "open",        "count":  8},
    {"status": "blocked",     "count":  2}
  ]
}
```
````

### Open tasks per agent

````
```json:chart
{
  "type": "bar",
  "title": "Open Tasks per Agent",
  "xKey": "agent",
  "yKeys": ["tasks"],
  "data": [
    {"agent": "Alice", "tasks": 4},
    {"agent": "Bob",   "tasks": 7},
    {"agent": "Carol", "tasks": 2}
  ]
}
```
````

### Velocity trend (multi-series area)

````
```json:chart
{
  "type": "area",
  "title": "Sprint Velocity",
  "xKey": "sprint",
  "yKeys": ["completed", "planned"],
  "xLabel": "Sprint",
  "yLabel": "Story Points",
  "data": [
    {"sprint": "S1", "completed": 18, "planned": 20},
    {"sprint": "S2", "completed": 22, "planned": 20},
    {"sprint": "S3", "completed": 17, "planned": 24},
    {"sprint": "S4", "completed": 25, "planned": 24}
  ]
}
```
````

