## Data sources

Always query the Mission Control API to collect real data before composing a
chart. Useful endpoints:

| Data needed | API path |
|---|---|
| Task list with statuses | `GET /api/v1/agent/boards/{{ board_id }}/tasks` |
| Sprint list | `GET /api/v1/agent/boards/{{ board_id }}/sprints` |
| Sprint tickets | `GET /api/v1/agent/boards/{{ board_id }}/sprints/{sprint_id}/tickets` |
| Board activity events | `GET /api/v1/agent/boards/{{ board_id }}/activity` |

Use `jq` to aggregate counts from the task list before building your `data` array.

---

## Posting a chart

Send a normal chat message that includes a `json:chart` fenced block. The block
can appear anywhere in the message body. Example (board chat):

```bash
curl -fsS -X POST "{{ base_url }}/api/v1/boards/{{ board_id }}/memory" \
  -H "X-Agent-Token: {{ auth_token }}" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "content": "Here is the sprint burndown:\n\n```json:chart\n{\"type\":\"line\",\"title\":\"Sprint Burndown\",\"xKey\":\"day\",\"yKeys\":[\"remaining\",\"ideal\"],\"data\":[{\"day\":\"Mon\",\"remaining\":24,\"ideal\":20}]}\n```",
    "tags": ["chat"]
  }'
```

For channel threads, POST to `{{ base_url }}/api/v1/threads/{thread_id}/messages`.

---

## Rules

- **Never fabricate data.** Always query the API and aggregate before charting.
- **Numbers only** for Y-axis values. Strings cause the chart to fall back to a
  code block without crashing.
- **Limit `data` to ≤ 500 rows.** Aggregate/summarise larger datasets first.
- A malformed JSON spec gracefully falls back to a styled code block in the UI —
  the user sees the raw JSON rather than an error.
